radiographic_examinations.findings: The central cardiac shadow with visible methyl methacrylate struts.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: At age 11 years, radiographs show incorporation of struts in the anterior chest wall without migration or fracture.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Four struts of methyl methacrylate covered with Marlex mesh, wired to the ribs to reconstruct the sternal defect.
The four methyl methacrylate struts are less visible.
